(laughs)

153
00:06:20,612 --> 00:06:22,146
Mr. Shue, Mercedes is here!

154
00:06:22,225 --> 00:06:23,926
- Oh, hey, Mercedes.
- Hi!

155
00:06:23,960 --> 00:06:26,128
I'd like to speak to a manager, please.

156
00:06:26,163 --> 00:06:27,463
What seems to be the problem here?

157
00:06:27,497 --> 00:06:28,998
WOMAN: Well, one hour ago,

158
00:06:29,032 --> 00:06:32,434
I got a call from Detective Sue Sylvester

159
00:06:32,469 --> 00:06:35,337
with the LAPD saying that
a 50-year-old Ohio man

160
00:06:35,372 --> 00:06:39,675
with a perm had abducted 12
emotionally disturbed teenagers,

161
00:06:39,709 --> 00:06:41,944
and if he tried to make a reservation,

162
00:06:41,978 --> 00:06:43,479
I was to contact the FBI.

163
00:06:44,848 --> 00:06:46,982
Oh, my God, that's them.

164
00:06:47,017 --> 00:06:49,151
Who?

165
00:06:49,186 --> 00:06:51,287
Do you seriously have no idea who that is?

166
00:06:51,321 --> 00:06:53,189
Do none of you read the show choir blogs?

167
00:06:53,223 --> 00:06:54,323
No, Blaine, we don't.

168
00:06:54,357 --> 00:06:56,659
None of us read the show
choir blogs. Just you.

169
00:06:56,693 --> 00:06:58,127
That's Throat Explosion.

170
00:06:58,161 --> 00:07:01,297
And that's their leader, Jean-Baptiste.

171
00:07:02,866 --> 00:07:05,067
Jean-Baptiste was born in
Quebec to acrobatic parents.

172
00:07:05,101 --> 00:07:07,736
He trained with Cirque du Soleil
before emigrating to Ft. Wayne

173
00:07:07,771 --> 00:07:09,338
where he used his
French-Canadian circus stylings

174
00:07:09,372 --> 00:07:11,307
to turn the entire show
choir world upside down.

175
00:07:11,341 --> 00:07:13,242
Bonjour !

176
00:07:13,276 --> 00:07:15,211
You must be the New Directions.

177
00:07:15,245 --> 00:07:18,180
And you... must be Blaine.

178
00:07:18,215 --> 00:07:21,283
How did you know my name?

179
00:07:21,318 --> 00:07:23,018
Show choir blogs.

180
00:07:23,053 --> 00:07:24,720
I'm, you know, I'm Sam Evans,

181
00:07:24,754 --> 00:07:26,522
and I'm the leader of the New Directions.

182
00:07:26,556 --> 00:07:29,225
And, you know, I know you guys
are all really good and stuff,

183
00:07:29,259 --> 00:07:31,527
but that's just gonna get
us out of our comfort zones

184
00:07:31,561 --> 00:07:32,761
and send us over the top.

185
00:07:32,796 --> 00:07:35,397
Well, it was really great to meet you, Sam.

186
00:07:35,432 --> 00:07:36,866
Best of luck, New Directions.

187
00:07:36,900 --> 00:07:39,869
We really can't wait to see your set.

188
00:07:39,903 --> 00:07:42,304
And crush you like a bug.

189
00:07:43,540 --> 00:07:44,573
Bye!

190
00:07:45,776 --> 00:07:46,976
Excuse me.

191
00:07:47,010 --> 00:07:48,577
What is with the turtlenecks?

192
00:07:52,349 --> 00:07:53,716
That was tense.

193
00:07:53,750 --> 00:07:58,053
Oh, I wouldn't miss this
show choir high school drama.

194
00:07:58,088 --> 00:08:00,189
Come on, tell me all about it. Let's go.

195
00:08:00,223 --> 00:08:02,324
Like a bug. That was good.
He was right here in my face.

196
00:08:02,359 --> 00:08:03,426
Why didn't I think of that?

197
00:08:03,460 --> 00:08:04,527
He smells like a winner.

198
00:08:12,269 --> 00:08:14,136
MAN (on TV): Another golden day
of sunshine here in Los Angeles.

199
00:08:14,171 --> 00:08:17,339
Hey, Marley, it's Ryder.
Can I come in for a minute?

200
00:08:21,011 --> 00:08:22,545
- Hi.
- Hi.

201
00:08:22,579 --> 00:08:24,547
Can I talk to you?

202
00:08:24,581 --> 00:08:26,382
- You can come in.
- Okay.

203
00:08:29,152 --> 00:08:32,555
Look, you and me are
probably never gonna happen.

204
00:08:32,589 --> 00:08:35,624
And... like, I'm slowly accepting that.

205
00:08:35,659 --> 00:08:38,394
But that doesn't mean
I don't care about you.

206
00:08:38,428 --> 00:08:40,029
Or that I don't occasionally look

207
00:08:40,063 --> 00:08:41,931
at your Facebook page to check your status.

208
00:08:41,965 --> 00:08:43,766
Single, and it's going to stay that way.

209
00:08:43,800 --> 00:08:45,601
Talking about where you
put what your job is.

210
00:08:45,635 --> 00:08:47,403
It used to say, "Singer/Songwriter,"

211
00:08:47,437 --> 00:08:49,071
now it just says "Undecided."

212
00:08:51,074 --> 00:08:54,777
I entered my songs into this contest.

213
00:08:54,811 --> 00:08:56,479
And you lost?

214
00:08:56,513 --> 00:08:59,882
Worse. I didn't hear back at all.

215
00:09:00,917 --> 00:09:02,251
And I took that as...

216
00:09:02,285 --> 00:09:03,753
I don't know... a wake-up call.

217
00:09:03,787 --> 00:09:05,788
Oh, come on. That's only one contest.

218
00:09:05,822 --> 00:09:09,592
Actually, I've entered a
bunch of contests, Ryder.

219
00:09:09,626 --> 00:09:12,828
Anyway, what's so wrong
with joining Accounting Club

220
00:09:12,863 --> 00:09:14,096
when we get back?

221
